Robin Cura | PhD in Geography and GIScience

Current position

Post-Doctoral researcher at UMR Gographie-cits and Deezer Research Team, within the RECORDS project.

Bio

Robin Cura is a Doctor in Geography, with a PhD thesis focused on quantitative geography, agent-based modelling and spatial data visualization. With a geographical information engineering scholarship, hes interested in the development and dissemination of quantitative methods for geographic data science and to the use of exploratory and visual spatual-data analysis.

Education

Universit Paris 1 Panthon-Sorbonne | Paris, France

  • Ph.D.in Geography within the Gographie-cits research lab | 2013 - 2020
    Thesis (in french) : Interdisciplinary modelling of settlement systems through the collective : co-construction and visual analysis of a simulation model

  • Master Carthago : Geography, GIScience and Cartography | 2008 - 2011
